"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156598","Home Office","false","2014-11-25","<p>The Home Office has an internal target of 10 days from the initial point of contact to the point the applicant attends the unit. This was introduced at the start of the current financial year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156598/answer",,,,,,,,,,"2014-11-25T16:16:18.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156598/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156598/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-11-19","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the (a) target and (b) actual average waiting time for asylum seekers to receive an appointment for an initial screening interview is.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","215259"
