"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156784","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-11-24","<p /> <p>The Youth Justice Board works with a range of partners to address the over-representation of Black and Minority Ethnic young people in the criminal justice system.</p><p> </p><p>The table below provides further details of the categories used to record Black, Asian and Minority Ethnic offenders in youth custody.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Ethnic Group </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Breakdown of ethnic group</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Black /Black British</p></td><td><p>Caribbean/African/Other Black</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Asian/Asian British</p></td><td><p>Indian/Pakistan/Bangladeshi/Other Asian</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mixed</p></td><td><p>White-Black Caribbean/White-Black African/White-Asian /Other Mixed</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Chinese/Other ethnic group</p></td><td><p>Chinese/other</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156784/answer",,,,,,,,,,"2014-11-24T17:57:14.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156784/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156784/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-19","Youth Custody","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 7 November 2014 to Question 213434, which individual ethnic groups made up the proportion of black, Asian and minority ethnic offenders in youth custody in each year since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","215244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156785","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-11-25","<p /> <p>The advisors to the review, appointed by Rory Stewart MP were: the Rt. Hon. Lord Judge, the former Lord Chief Justice of England and Wales; Lord Ramsbotham GCB CBE, formerly HM Chief Inspector of Prisons for England and Wales; Sir John Nutting Bt. QC, who was commissioned by the Howard League for Penal Re-form to conduct its enquiry into former armed service personnel in the prison population; Dr Hugh Milroy OBE, the Chief Executive of Veterans Aid (who also advised Sir John Nutting in relation to his enquiry); and Major General Michael Laurie CBE, a member of Lord Ashcroft’s Veterans Transition Review Team.</p><p> </p><p>Stephen Phillips has submitted his completed review to the Secretary of State and it will be published shortly.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156785/answer",,,,,,,,,,"2014-11-25T11:35:49.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156785/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156785/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-19","Criminal Proceedings: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 18 November 2014 to Question 211583, who the advisers to the review of veterans in the criminal justice system are.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","215243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156786","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-11-24","<p /> <p>Youth Offending Teams (YOTs) play a key part in the youth justice system and the Government recognises their valuable contribution to the recent successes of the system. We want to improve our understanding of how YOTs are operating and how they have evolved in light of the changing circumstances surrounding the delivery of local youth justice services. We are working closely with the Youth Justice Board to finalise the details of this stocktake, which will establish a clearer picture of how the YOT model is operating nationwide.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","215236 ; 215327 ; 215328","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156786/answer",,,,,,,,,,"2014-11-24T17:59:19.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156786/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/156786/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-19","Youth Offending Teams","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many officials from his Department are working on the Youth Offending Team Stock Take announced by the Minister for Prisons, Probation and Rehabilitation on 17 November 2014.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","215235"
